description: For every positive integer m, let u(m) = (d(1),d(2),...,d(k)) be the unitary divisors of m in increasing order. Let Q be the concatenation of the vectors (d(k)/d(1), d(k-1)/d(2), ..., d(1)/d(k)), so that every positive rational number appears in Q exactly once. The numerators form A229994; the denominators, A077610.
